  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Objective: To compare the effect of guided tissue regeneration (GTR) + concentrated growth
      factors (CGF) + bone graft and CGF + bone graft in the treat of II° furcations of human
      mandibular molars. Methods: At least thirty II°furcation involvements in mandibular molars
      will be included and randomly divided into two groups. The experimental group will accept GTR
      + CGF + bone graft therapy, and the control group will accept CGF + bone graft therapy. The
      clinical examination and cone beam computed tomography (CBCT) will be performed at baseline
      and 1 year post-surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
